text: Acleris aenigmana is a species of moth of the family Tortricidae. It is found in North America, where it has been recorded from California and Utah. Adults have been recorded on wing in April, June and October.mothphotographersgroup The larvae feed on Hypericum perforatum and Prunus emarginata.Tortricidae Food Plant Database ==References== Category:Moths described in 1964 aenigmana Category:Moths of North America
